">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">η</span> : <span class=\"fn\">B</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hη</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Norm/Defs.html#Algebra.norm\">Algebra.norm</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Defs.html#algebraMap\">algebraMap</a> <span class=\"fn\">B</span> <span class=\"fn\">L</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">η</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">ε</span> : <span class=\"fn\">B</span>), <span class=\"fn\">ε</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\">η</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/IntegralClosure/IntegralRestrict.html#galRestrict\">galRestrict</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span> <span class=\"fn\">K</span> <span class=\"fn\">L</span> <span class=\"fn\">B</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">g</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">ε</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">ε</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The integral version of the classical formulation of Hilbert's theorem 90: in the `ABKL`\nsetting, suppose that `L/K` is a finite Galois extension such that the Galois group is cyclic\ngenerated by `g` and let `η : B` be an element of norm `1` (when viewed as an element of `L`).\nThen there exists `ε : B` such that `ε ≠ 0` and `η * g ε = ε`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RepresentationTheory/Homological/GroupCohomology/Hilbert90.html#groupCohomology.exists_mul_galRestrict_of_norm_eq_one","kind":"theorem","line":162,"name":"groupCohomology.exists_mul_g