ss=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#IsCyclic\">IsCyclic</a> <span class=\"fn\">Gal(<span class=\"fn\">L</span>/<span class=\"fn\">K</span>)</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">g</span> : <span class=\"fn\">Gal(<span class=\"fn\">L</span>/<span class=\"fn\">K</span>)</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hg</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">Gal(<span class=\"fn\">L</span>/<span class=\"fn\">K</span>)</span>), <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Subgroup/ZPowers/Basic.html#Subgroup.zpowers\">Subgroup.zpowers</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">L</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hx</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Norm/Defs.html#Algebra.norm\">Algebra.norm</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">y</span> : <span class=\"fn\">L</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Units/Defs.html#Units\">ˣ</a>), <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">y</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">y</span></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Hilbert's Theorem 90: given a finite cyclic Galois extension `L/K`, an element `x : L` such\nthat `N_{L/K}(x) = 1`, and a generator `g` of `Gal(L/K)`, there exists `y : Lˣ`\nsuch that `y/g y = x`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RepresentationTheory/Homological/GroupCohomology/Hilbert90.html#groupCohomology.exists_div_of_norm_eq_one","kind":"theorem","line":131,"name":"groupCohomology.exists_div_of_norm_eq_one","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RepresentationTheory/Homological/GroupCohomology/Hilbert90.lean#L131-L154"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RepresentationTheory/Homological/GroupCohomology/Hilbert90.html#groupCohomology.norm_ofAlgebraAutOnUnits_eq\"><span class=\"name\">groupCohomology</span>.<span class=\"name\">norm_ofAlgebraAutOnUnits_eq</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">K </span><span class=\"fn\">L</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">L</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Defs.html#Algebra\">Algebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span> <span class=\"fn\">L</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/FiniteDimensional/Defs.html#FiniteDimensional\